    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I had a look into this issue (my first work on this repo here), but it seems that the committee cache for the next epoch is not always initialized.\r\n\r\nI created a small test (see https://github.com/blacktemplar/lighthouse/commit/5ebcd445ab132114b4f42a4b3eff4bfa925b2b58#diff-92db90820111e19dbba60be6248191cf) for this and for example the following test run prints some uninitialized messages:\r\n\r\n`cargo test --package beacon_chain --release finalizes_with_full_participation -- --nocapture`\r\n\r\nThe ouput being:\r\n\r\n```\r\n     Running target/release/deps/tests-bfb1313740770fc5\r\n\r\nrunning 1 test\r\ncached epoch next was uninitialized: CommitteeCacheUninitialized(Next)\r\ncached epoch next was uninitialized: CommitteeCacheUninitialized(Next)\r\ncached epoch next was uninitialized: CommitteeCacheUninitialized(Next)\r\ncached epoch next was uninitialized: CommitteeCacheUninitialized(Next)\r\ntest finalizes_with_full_participation ... ok\r\n```\r\n\r\nAm I doing something wrong or is this another bug?",
